hu.elte.txtuml.api

Class ModelType<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • hu.elte.txtuml.api.ModelType<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the Java type of the primitive type this object represents
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelElement, ModelValue
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ModelBool, ModelInt, ModelString

    public class ModelType<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelValue
    Base class for immutable classes representing primitive types in the model. Use of the Java primitive types and Strings is completely disallowed in the model, except for parameters of constructors and setter methods of ModelType and VariableType classes and their subclasses, and logging methods of Action ( log, logError ).

    Represents: subclasses represent primitive values

    Usage:

    Should not be used directly. Instead, use its subclasses: ModelBool, ModelInt, ModelString

    Java restrictions:

    • Instantiate: disallowed
    • Define subtype: disallowed

    See the documentation of Model for an overview on modeling in txtUML.

    Author:
    Gabor Ferenc Kovacs
    See Also:
    ModelBool, ModelInt, ModelString
